<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Harvey</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 131.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 22, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatches—No. 260, of the 20th
                            ultimo, and No. 261, of the 22d ultimo—have been received. The latter
                            has been referred for perusal to the Secretary of the Navy.</p>
                        <pb facs="0294" n="270" xml:id="pg_270"/>
                        <p>The promptness and energy manifested by the authorities at the Azores in
                            carrying out the instructions of the home government concerning rebel
                            cruisers which may seek to rendezvous at those islands is very
                            satisfactory, and your own activity and vigilance in connexion with
                            these matters is highly appreciated.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Lisbon.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>